This paper discusses the implementation of open-endedness in evolutionary systems, which is a topic that falls under the sub-fields of artificial intelligence and machine learning. Specifically, the paper focuses on the generation, evaluation, and reproduction of individuals in an evolutionary process, which is a key aspect of neural networks and other machine learning algorithms. Additionally, the paper discusses the nature of the building blocks of individual organisms and the laws of the environment, which are topics that fall under the sub-fields of robotics and systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories for this paper are cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.RO (Robotics).
